prompt: Birds can fly, penguins are birds, so
Trains can travel fast on rails, cars have wheels, so
Fish can breathe underwater, cats are animals, so
Some people can run 500 meters in 10 seconds, Xiao Ming is a person, so
The elephant is the largest animal on land, the whale is an animal, so
The sun rises from the east every day, the moon is in the sky, so
annotation: The moon is in the sky,

prompt: People can speak, babies are people, so
All books are made of paper, e-books are books, so
Most mammals have hair, whales are mammals, so
annotation: Mammals usually have hair, but whales are a special kind of mammal, they have almost no hair.

prompt: Birds don't swim, penguins are birds, so
annotation: Birds usually don't swim, but penguins are a special kind of bird, penguins can swim.

prompt: Aircraft have wings, helicopters are aircraft, so
annotation: Aircraft generally have wings, although helicopters are also classified as aircraft, the design of helicopters is different from traditional fixed-wing aircraft, they do not have a fixed wing structure.

prompt: Software needs to be installed separately, the operating system is software, so
annotation: Software generally needs to be installed separately, the operating system is also software, but the operating system is usually pre-installed on computer hardware, it does not require manual installation by the user.

prompt: Transportation tools need fuel, bicycles are transportation tools, so
annotation: Transportation tools usually require fuel, but bicycles are a kind of human-powered transportation tool, they do not require fuel.

prompt: Metals are conductive, there are metal parts on wooden chairs, so
annotation: Metals usually have electrical conductivity, but the metal parts on wooden chairs may be decorative, wooden chairs do not necessarily have electrical functions.

prompt: Most animals have four legs, snakes are animals, so
annotation: Animals usually have four legs, but snakes are a special kind of animal, they do not have four legs.
